    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get that, but my doctor is super strict and always leaves me on high doses even when i'm not eating much. i'm just worried about waking up with like a 40 or 50 reading cause i feel so low tonight. if i just skip the basal dose tonight, isn't it safer than taking way too much insulin for almost no food? wouldn't my body just use its own reserves?",
